# Ashed credentials â€” optional, never required for auth

**Ashed connection keys / JWTs are NOT part of any authentication or onboarding flow.** Do not gate member link, Discord user link, alliance invite accept, or guild registration on Ashed credentials unless the feature explicitly consumes Ashed API data.

## What auth flows use instead

| Flow | Proof | Storage |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Web member onboarding (`/onboard`, member-link wizard) | In-game **name + UID** â†’ Last War lookup + roster match | `hq_member_links`, `alliance_memberships` |
| Discord member link (`/link`, `/link-commander`) | Same **name + UID** proof in guild's alliance | `discord_member_links` |
| Discord guild registration (`/link-alliance`) | Owner via **member link** (`callerIsAllianceOwner`) or platform maintainer | `discord_guild_alliances` |
| HQ web session | Email / OAuth â†’ `hq_users` + session | Session cookie |

**Never** require `discord_hq_links` or an Ashed connection key for a member to link their in-game commander on Discord.

## When Ashed credentials ARE used (optional follow-up)

Ashed is an **optional upgrade** after identity is established. It enables:

- **Roster sync** and iframe tools on HQ web (connect flow)
- **Bot roster reads** via `alliance_ashed_credentials` (`/link-to-ashed-seat`)
- **Video processing** (only when the user has the processing role)
- **Legacy owner proof** via Ashed owner JWT on `/link-to-ashed-seat` (parallel to native owner member-link proof)

`/link-to-ashed-seat` â†’ `/discord/authorize` with `purpose=alliance_credentials` is the **only** Discord browser flow that accepts an Ashed connection key.

`/link` â†’ `/discord/authorize` with `purpose=user_link` accepts **in-game name + UID**, not an Ashed key.

## Implementation guardrails

- Do not add `verifyBase44Connection`, `parseConnectionInput`, or connection-key form fields to member link or onboarding paths.
- Do not return `errors.hqLinkRequired` before member-link or guild-registration handlers â€” those flows do not depend on `discord_hq_links`.
- `discord_hq_links` remains for **web Discord OAuth** and platform-maintainer HQ identity; it is not a prerequisite for bot member commands.
- Bot paths stay **read-only** on Ashed unless a future feature documents mutating calls with owner JWT + audit.

